album.description_preview:
Voyage is ABBA’s long-awaited ninth studio album, set to be released on November 5, 2021 – exactly 39 years, 11 months, and 6 days since the group’s previous studio album, The Visitors. The first two singles from the album, “I Still Have Faith In You” and “Don’t Shut Me Down”, were released on September 2, 2021, alongisde a YouTube live stream announcing the album and accompanying ABBAtar hologram concert.

Soon after first reuniting in 2016 to celebrate the 50th anniversary of Bjorn Ulveaus and Benny Andersson – ABBA’s principle songwriters – first meeting, the group announced that they were planning to create digital avatars that would go on tour and play the group’s greatest hits. Not long after this announcement, ABBA began to record two new songs, “I Still Have Faith In You” and “Don’t Shut Me Down”, which were announced in 2018. Due to delays in getting the project together, the group later announced that 5 new songs would be released in 2019. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the project was delayed and ABBA decided to record a full album. Meanwhile, for the hologram concert, a facility called the “ABBA Arena” was built in London, England to host it.

Among the eight brand new songs, the album will also include “Just A Notion”, originally intended for inclusion on the Thank You for the Music box set in 1994, only to be rejected due to mixing issues, and instead only included as a small snippet in the “ABBA Undeleted” medley. The song was originally recorded in 1978 during early sessions for ABBA’s sixth studio album, Voulez-Vous.

accepted_by.about_me_summary:
Earthling from Roswell, NM, residing in NYC & Miami;
Heavy into music and lyrics, I’m a singer/songwriter/lyricist, founder of Neuro (the band) aka Neuro NYC

Neuro album 1: “Mind Altar”
Synaptic-website: click to Neuro’s site

Neuro’s 2nd album, “Sensory Overlord”, will be released incrementally starting in 2022, due to a post-dystopian monetary slump.  Contextual Bowie Lyric,

it’s the theater of financiers
Count them, fifteen ‘round a table
White and dressed to kill

Neuro is a politically charged art-rock project/band with prog-like sci-fi elements and psychic undertones.

And I’m nuts, or rather an MBTI INFP IDR Labs.
Natal chart?  Cancer-Leo/Virgo Rising/Taurus moon, with 3 orbs in the 11th House of Aquarius; not that I believe in Astrology, it does drive Queen’s crest (below).  My musical influences include, surprise,
01.  Queen
02.  Muse
03.  David Bowie
